  "question": (a) Find the method of moments estimate for $\theta$ based on a random sample of size $n$ taken from the following probability density function

$$
f(x)=(\theta+1) x^\theta \quad \text { for } \quad 0<x<1 .
$$

(b) Calculate the estimate of $\theta$ for the sample $x_1=0.7, x_2=0.4, x_3=0.8, x_4=$ 0.5",
  "data": null,
  "answer": "(a) $\hat{\theta}=\frac{2 \bar{x}-1}{1-\bar{x}}$
(b) $\hat{\theta}=\frac{2(0.6)-1}{1-0.6}=0.5$",
